content: Amazing Game as always
Like the game! Altho it was kinda short unlike crystalline. Also lookinh forward to your new vn!

Game is smooth and flawless and animations are really great.My problem is story well not that its bad it's just it was not as deep as other pixelfade games (AA,KAS, CRYSTALLINE)and feels a little boring in some points as there no base goals in story in all previous games there is deep mystery or main objective well this game has it but objective fade in middle and mystery result was not as rewarding but I think you should purchase if have some free time .I hope next VN will be deep for readers.
I just wish we could preview the CG scenes we got from playing the game.
Best
i want MOAR!!!! was too short!

I need MOAR ,seriously all your games are masterpiece for me lol I hope you guys make some long story, I mean it's not that short but after that sweet time in end I thought there will be more like there future life or something well it's just an idea xD But overall it's all good üëç looking forward for your next game^_^
Epic
Dont like anime but love this and the rest of the games pixlefade makes

Ethereal Enigma was sooo good. I saw multiple ratings saying that game is super short, but there are multiple endings, and a lot of game time. It took me a few days to get all the way through and see every ending. This is one of the absolute best visual novels I have ever read through and played. PixelFade outdid themselves again with this game. I wish I could give it more than five stars. I highly recommend this to anyone looking to have a good time and find a great story. Absolute masterpiece.
Just didn't have as much excitement as the previous work Crystalline. Additionally, the skip button is/was broken and necesitates clicking through all text.
I liked it, but it feels like a step back from Crystalline in terms of narrative complexity. Nevertheless, I eagerly look forward to the next Pixelfade title.

This is a MUST play. I've played all of pixelfades' games and have enjoyed every single one of them. It has a nice story with good pacing, interesting characters, a lot of easter eggs to previous games like crystalline and ace academy. The game overall is a very good way to just sit back and escape reality for a second, if you're questioning whether or not to buy this game: buy it, you won't regret it. (If you like this game, you should check out other titles from pixelfade)
Once again, a very well done visual novel by Pixelfade. Good story, great characters and voice acting.

Pixelfade did it again! I always love their games. The story is really good and it really makes you care about the characters. My first playthrough took me around 10 and a half hours so there is plenty of content here. And there is still incentive to play it more than once in order to see the stuff you can do with the different characters. The only problem is that I'm not able to change the skip feature to all to unread. was hoping to use that for my second playthrough. That's the only bug tbh.

Overall Game is Good, Perfect story. I love how there's a side character from previous games fit in the script. But Lacks of illustration in some scene, that's a pity. The ending is not like how I expected, I prefer if the story would be forward 2 or 3 years to view their future, cuz you just left me hanging before credit (same like Ace Academy). Maybe Cristallyne ending with the protagonist and main heroine finally receive happy ending would be good. Hoping for sequel or new games tho.
ive played through all 3 other games and theyre fantastic i know this will be no different ace academy 2 would be awsome just saying
Great story and characters again from Pixelfade and it never disappoints me. The reason I gave this a 4 is because the skip (with unread option) is not working. Pls. fix.

The story is good. The only problem I've had is when i finished my first playthrough and tried to start the second one the skip feature didn't work. I went to options so I could change it to skip all but that still didn't work. I've also been wondering why you guys stopped adding the gallery in your games after ace academy.
I Know this game is going to be great can't wait to play it
"What is a Kosei?" lol By the way the last name Dawn reminded me of Leanna Dawn from Crystalline, Almost thought they are related in a way. Good work Pixelfade
Played through the previous 3. Had a blast with them all! I know this one will be just as good if not better!
Definitely another top project by PF man this release was a shocker gotta love the effort and the endless puns and references topped it off for a great VN
